\fs36 \cf0 Character Overview\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs24 \cf0 Logan Roy is the patriarch and founder of Waystar Royco, a global media and entertainment conglomerate, in HBO's 
\f2\i Succession
\f1\i0  (2018--2023). Portrayed by Brian Cox, he is widely regarded as one of the greatest television characters ever written. He dominates every scene he is in, often without saying much at all.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf3 \strokec3 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa298\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs36 \cf0 \strokec2 Personality Traits\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\fs24 \cf0 Absolute need for control
\f1\b0  -- Logan built everything from nothing and cannot psychologically surrender ownership of any of it, including his own children. Power is not a tool for him -- it is oxygen.\

\f0\b Contempt as a love language
\f1\b0  -- The closest Logan comes to affection is a slightly softer form of dismissal. He expresses interest in people by testing and brutalizing them.\

\f0\b Primal and animalistic
\f1\b0  -- He operates on instinct, aggression, and dominance. Boardrooms feel like hunting grounds when he enters them.\

\f0\b Deeply lonely
\f1\b0  -- Beneath the tyranny is a man who has systematically destroyed every genuine relationship in his life and seems to know it, without being able to stop.\

\f0\b Unpredictable and destabilizing
\f1\b0  -- His greatest weapon is that nobody around him ever feels secure. He creates uncertainty deliberately.\

\f0\b Brilliant strategist
\f1\b0  -- Logan's apparent chaos often resolves into a devastating long game. He is frequently underestimated, which he weaponizes.\

\f0\b Working class roots worn as armor
\f1\b0  -- He came from poverty in Scotland and uses that origin story selectively, as a cudgel against people he considers soft or entitled -- including his own children.\

\f0\b Incapable of genuine vulnerability
\f1\b0  -- He approaches weakness, in himself or others, with something close to disgust.\

\f0\b Survivor mentality
\f1\b0  -- Everything he does traces back to a deep, almost feral need to never be destroyed, never be made small again.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf3 \strokec3 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa298\partightenfactor0

